cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with ad hoc network capacity and transmission rules. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses channel inversion power control and its impact on capacity. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper addresses the impact of threshold-based scheduling on capacity. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper discusses a fully distributed scheme for transmission. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper employs tools from stochastic geometry to obtain bounds on the distribution of the signal-to-interference level.
